WEBVTT

00:09.443 --> 00:13.247
Look,
let's just both take a breath.

00:15.383 --> 00:17.651
My mama slaps me harder
than that.

00:17.685 --> 00:21.622
<i>True immortality rests
in a pure and mighty will...</i>

00:23.324 --> 00:26.594
<i>...for history isn't written
by the feeble masses.</i>

00:26.627 --> 00:29.563
<i>It is written and rewritten
by soldiers</i>

00:29.597 --> 00:31.031
<i>carrying the banner of kings.</i>

00:31.065 --> 00:34.535
There she is, machos.
Our destiny.

00:34.568 --> 00:37.104
<i>That is what it means
to be strong.</i>

00:37.138 --> 00:39.407
I want you to know
that I fired those bastards.

00:41.275 --> 00:43.778
They had no right roughing
you up the way they did.

00:47.081 --> 00:48.482
You are the first person
that I am aware of

00:48.516 --> 00:50.184
to publicly accuse
the president

00:50.217 --> 00:52.219
of responsibility
for the Watergate break-in.

00:52.253 --> 00:53.587
Pretty sure
I won't be the last.

00:53.621 --> 00:56.223
How do you feel about your wife
potentially speaking to the Senate?

00:56.257 --> 00:59.293
Well, I support Martha
in whatever she decides to do.

00:59.326 --> 01:01.061
I'm testifying on Monday.

01:01.095 --> 01:02.229
<i>They said
the judge was sending you</i>

01:02.263 --> 01:04.799
to a bad prison
for a long time.

01:04.832 --> 01:06.267
When I was a boy,

01:06.300 --> 01:10.104
my only friend was my nanny,
Frau Teresa.

01:10.137 --> 01:12.406
She told me the story of a boy

01:12.440 --> 01:14.375
who, from the power
of his own will,

01:14.408 --> 01:16.677
<i>became the leader
of her Fatherland.</i>

01:16.710 --> 01:20.815
She made me realize that I, too,
could choose to be strong.

01:20.848 --> 01:23.217
This will be
Father's trial by fire.

01:23.250 --> 01:25.186
I'm at the center
of this thing.

01:25.219 --> 01:26.454
I mean, that guy--

01:26.487 --> 01:28.589
Well, what if you're the guy
who saw an injustice

01:28.622 --> 01:31.192
and decided to do something
about it?

01:31.225 --> 01:32.793
Mr. Dean, Mr. Dean,
how do you feel?

01:32.827 --> 01:35.196
Everyone seems to think
you did pretty darn good.

01:35.229 --> 01:37.364
I hear Martha is on deck
for Thursday.

01:37.398 --> 01:40.367
The problem...

01:40.401 --> 01:42.603
with loving something too much

01:42.636 --> 01:44.271
is that you can't do
what needs to be done.

01:46.774 --> 01:49.276
I trust you'll do
what needs to be done.

02:12.333 --> 02:14.802
<i>♪ I'd like ♪</i>

02:14.835 --> 02:19.840
<i>♪ Just one
Old-fashioned Christmas ♪</i>

02:23.511 --> 02:27.281
I don't, uh, know
where I end up on this thing.

02:27.314 --> 02:31.785
According to this, I was born
in the Year of the Rat.

02:31.819 --> 02:36.790
Says I'm bright, patient,
and inspiring to others.

02:36.824 --> 02:39.493
Somebody's been reading
your mail.

02:39.527 --> 02:40.828
Fuck off.

02:40.861 --> 02:44.365
It also says
I can be happy on my own

02:44.398 --> 02:47.535
or make an outstanding partner.

02:47.568 --> 02:49.203
I'll be sure
to inform your wife.

02:51.238 --> 02:52.706
Yeah, good idea.

02:55.743 --> 02:57.211
What's going on
with these girls?

02:57.244 --> 02:58.879
I thought they were supposed
to be here at seven.

02:58.913 --> 03:01.682
John, you're not screening them
for the secretarial pool.

03:01.715 --> 03:04.318
As long as they know
their way around an inseam--

03:04.351 --> 03:05.619
I don't think they heard you
in the kitchen.

03:05.653 --> 03:07.555
Who gives a shit?

03:07.588 --> 03:09.857
Nobody speaky
the Engrish around here.

03:11.892 --> 03:13.193
You're a terrible man.

03:13.227 --> 03:14.428
I've learned it all from you.

03:14.461 --> 03:15.829
But before they do come in,

03:15.863 --> 03:17.731
there's something you should
probably know about your girl.

03:17.765 --> 03:19.533
I-I...
Don't tell me she's a cryer.

03:19.567 --> 03:20.701
I can't deal
with another cryer.

03:20.734 --> 03:23.938
No, nothing like that.
But she's married.

03:28.742 --> 03:29.843
Married?

03:30.744 --> 03:32.279
- Not happily.
- Oh, Christ.

03:32.313 --> 03:34.415
As though I-I don't have
enough stress in my life.

03:34.448 --> 03:35.716
So she's married.

03:35.749 --> 03:37.451
You've been with married girls
before, and this...

03:37.484 --> 03:40.621
this broad's got a rack
like Claudia Cardinale.

03:40.654 --> 03:42.756
You're gonna love her.
Trust me.

03:42.790 --> 03:44.658
She's a real alley cat, boy.

03:44.692 --> 03:46.393
Yeah, I should go.

03:46.427 --> 03:47.861
No, why?

03:47.895 --> 03:50.698
Because these girls
are 20 minutes late,

03:50.731 --> 03:53.233
and the only marriage
I can stand getting in the way of

03:53.267 --> 03:54.501
right now is my own.

03:54.535 --> 03:56.537
Come on, don't be like this, John.

03:56.570 --> 03:58.772
Look. Hey, speak of the devil.

03:58.806 --> 04:00.874
Ladies,
we've been waiting for you.

04:00.908 --> 04:05.279
Sorry. It was bumper-to-bumper
all the way to Columbus Circle.

04:05.312 --> 04:08.282
<i>Hey, John,
this is Peggy Quinn.</i>

04:09.650 --> 04:10.884
- Pleasure.
- <i>And, uh,</i>

04:10.918 --> 04:12.319
<i>I'm sorry, darling.
What's your name again?</i>

04:12.353 --> 04:15.356
- Martha Jennings.
- <i>Martha Jennings.</i>

04:15.389 --> 04:17.925
<i>John Mitchell,
meet Martha Jennings.</i>

04:17.958 --> 04:19.460
I'm-I'm John.

04:20.828 --> 04:22.696
I heard.

04:22.730 --> 04:23.897
Are you going somewhere?

04:24.898 --> 04:27.735
Uh, no, I was, uh--

04:27.768 --> 04:29.470
Looking for the coatroom.

04:29.503 --> 04:31.472
Yes, could you take this?
Thank you.

04:31.505 --> 04:32.773
Could you point me
toward the restroom?

04:32.806 --> 04:34.608
No, no, no. I'll walk you.
It's right over there.

04:34.642 --> 04:36.043
Okay, great. Thank you.

04:36.276 --> 04:37.277
Would you?

04:37.311 --> 04:39.613
Oh, sure. Sorry.

04:40.814 --> 04:41.915
Thank you.

04:41.949 --> 04:43.017
Sir?

04:43.050 --> 04:45.552
Yes, thank you. Uh, may I?

04:45.586 --> 04:47.621
<i>♪ Wait for Santa to sail in ♪</i>

04:47.655 --> 04:51.592
<i>♪ With your presents
In a canoe... ♪</i>

05:00.768 --> 05:04.438
So, uh,
Peggy tells me you're married.

05:07.474 --> 05:11.512
Well, evidently,
Peggy likes to talk.

05:11.545 --> 05:13.480
That she does.

05:13.514 --> 05:17.051
Ken tells me the same
about you, marriage-wise.

05:17.084 --> 05:20.487
Wow, those two are cut
from the same cloth.

05:20.521 --> 05:21.855
Absolute vipers.

05:21.889 --> 05:23.390
Mm.

05:26.460 --> 05:27.928
Can I come
a little closer to you?

05:32.032 --> 05:35.402
Now, there's one thing
you can say for marriage.

05:35.436 --> 05:37.538
Makes everything beyond it

05:37.571 --> 05:38.839
a little more fun.

05:40.841 --> 05:43.644
Little more, uh, beautiful.

05:48.382 --> 05:50.784
Oh, um...

05:50.818 --> 05:52.986
it's a little...
you have an eyelash.

05:57.524 --> 06:00.394
Yeah, make a wish.

06:00.427 --> 06:03.530
You know,
I don't believe in wishes.

06:03.564 --> 06:05.632
Well, I don't believe
in wasting them.

06:05.666 --> 06:07.534
<i>♪ ...Christmas ♪</i>

06:07.568 --> 06:11.438
<i>♪ On Christmas Island ♪</i>

06:12.806 --> 06:15.743
<i>♪ You will never stray,
For every day... ♪</i>

06:15.776 --> 06:16.777
What was it?

06:16.810 --> 06:18.579
Mm-mm. I can't tell you.

06:18.612 --> 06:21.415
That's the first rule
of wishes.

06:21.448 --> 06:23.417
But I do hope
it pans out for you.

06:23.450 --> 06:26.019
Really, I do.

06:26.053 --> 06:27.654
It's a doozy.

06:30.090 --> 06:32.960
Wow.

06:32.993 --> 06:35.462
- Can I get you a drink?
- Yes, please.

06:35.496 --> 06:36.864
And what would you like?

06:36.897 --> 06:37.998
Gin and tonic.

06:39.166 --> 06:43.003
Sir, can I get the lady
a gin and tonic, please?

06:43.036 --> 06:44.404
Thank you.

07:51.038 --> 07:52.706
Where is everybody?

07:52.739 --> 07:57.711
Your lawyer opted
for a closed-door session, Ms. Mitchell.

07:57.744 --> 08:01.481
No press. Take a seat.

08:01.515 --> 08:04.017
Now, we've got
a long day ahead of us,

08:04.051 --> 08:07.120
so let's get to it.

08:07.154 --> 08:11.725
I understand, uh, you have
an opening statement prepared.

08:11.758 --> 08:13.160
Yes, Sam. Thank you.

08:13.193 --> 08:14.828
<i>Mr. Chairman, before we begin,</i>

08:14.862 --> 08:17.965
I would just like to register
the minority's skepticism

08:17.998 --> 08:21.635
regarding the relevance
of Mrs. Mitchell's testimony.

08:21.668 --> 08:24.872
It's still unclear to me
what official role

08:24.905 --> 08:26.573
she held
within the administration.

08:26.607 --> 08:29.710
Senator Gurney,
as Mrs. Mitchell's counsel stipulated,

08:29.743 --> 08:33.647
she maintained an official
public relations role

08:33.680 --> 08:35.282
within
the Committee to Re-Elect.

08:35.515 --> 08:37.050
Mm-hmm.

08:37.084 --> 08:38.685
Doing what,
appearing on game shows?

08:38.719 --> 08:40.187
Ed, that's--

08:40.220 --> 08:41.655
Now just hold on a second.

08:41.688 --> 08:43.156
I was employed in the campaign

08:43.190 --> 08:45.225
at the direct request
of the president.

08:45.259 --> 08:46.793
Oh, and I'm sure

08:46.827 --> 08:50.731
we're all very appreciative
of your tireless dedication

08:50.764 --> 08:51.865
to your own celebrity...

08:51.899 --> 08:53.166
Pardon me?

08:53.200 --> 08:54.835
...but I'm still unsure
what any of that has to do

08:54.868 --> 08:57.704
with the matters that, uh, we are
examining in this committee.

08:57.738 --> 08:59.873
Honestly, Ed,
this is beneath you.

08:59.907 --> 09:01.775
Senator Gurney will suffice.

09:01.808 --> 09:04.711
Not according to your wife.

09:04.745 --> 09:06.079
- Mr. Chairman.
- Order.

09:06.113 --> 09:08.715
With all due respect,
there are significant facts

09:08.749 --> 09:12.786
that this witness
has failed to disclose.

09:12.819 --> 09:15.122
I would like to submit
this official report

09:15.155 --> 09:17.624
from Bellevue Hospital.

09:17.658 --> 09:19.760
<i>So submitted.</i>

09:20.928 --> 09:21.995
It indicates that

09:22.029 --> 09:24.064
Mrs. Mitchell
was institutionalized

09:24.097 --> 09:25.832
<i>after the birth
of her daughter,</i>

09:25.866 --> 09:27.668
<i>January of 1961.</i>

09:29.336 --> 09:33.106
It was given to me
by a close, personal source.

09:37.110 --> 09:39.913
Your father suffered
from acute mental illness,

09:39.947 --> 09:41.114
just like you.

09:41.148 --> 09:43.216
Isn't that so?

09:43.250 --> 09:46.687
I do not suffer
from acute mental illness.

09:50.924 --> 09:52.092
<i>In interviews,</i>

09:52.125 --> 09:53.961
<i>you have stated
that your father</i>

09:53.994 --> 09:58.966
<i>died in a car accident,
but that isn't true, is it?</i>

09:58.999 --> 10:00.600
<i>In fact, he, uh...</i>

10:00.634 --> 10:02.803
<i>he was
a drunken, degenerate gambler,</i>

10:02.836 --> 10:06.640
<i>a fanaticist prone
to paranoia, delusion,</i>

10:06.673 --> 10:08.809
and, ultimately, suicide.

10:08.842 --> 10:10.978
What's your point, Ed?

10:11.011 --> 10:14.147
<i>Isn't it possible
that your instability</i>

10:14.181 --> 10:17.718
<i>could perhaps have been
passed down from your father?</i>

10:17.751 --> 10:20.921
Could it be that--that
that's why you see conspiracies

10:20.954 --> 10:24.091
and plots where--
where none, in fact, exist?

10:31.298 --> 10:33.934
<i>'Cause if there is an issue
with her mental stability--</i>

10:33.967 --> 10:35.402
There are no issues.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.738
<i>Then why risk your marriage?</i>

10:37.771 --> 10:40.140
<i>Why risk
your husband's position?</i>

10:48.749 --> 10:52.786
Mrs. Mitchell, why risk the happiness
of your own daughter?

10:55.222 --> 10:57.124
Because it's the truth.

10:58.692 --> 11:00.927
It is the truth.

11:00.961 --> 11:03.697
And what about your husband?

11:03.730 --> 11:06.867
Does he share your
understanding of the truth?

11:21.214 --> 11:22.983
What the fuck are you doing?

11:27.988 --> 11:29.322
What are you doing?

11:29.356 --> 11:31.358
You told them everything.

11:31.391 --> 11:33.226
Told who what?
What are you talking about?

11:33.260 --> 11:35.028
<i>You know exactly
what I'm talking about.</i>

11:35.062 --> 11:36.163
You set me up.

11:36.196 --> 11:40.367
You gave them the knife, and you told them
exactly where to stick it!

11:40.400 --> 11:43.403
Sweetheart,
I only wanted to keep you

11:43.437 --> 11:46.840
on the right side
of this whole goddamn thing.

11:46.873 --> 11:48.809
You're the one
who wanted to testify.

11:51.044 --> 11:53.080
Oh, my God,
you're driving me crazy!

11:53.113 --> 11:56.016
<i>You make me feel
like I am losing my mind!</i>

11:56.049 --> 11:57.451
<i>What's going on?</i>

11:57.484 --> 11:58.785
<i>Go back to your room, honey.</i>

11:58.819 --> 11:59.920
- <i>But--</i>
- Now!

12:01.221 --> 12:03.924
<i>Oh, cleaning up
after Martha again.</i>

12:03.957 --> 12:05.258
I've grown so used to it.

12:05.292 --> 12:07.094
<i>Big John Mitchell,
lord of the manor,</i>

12:07.127 --> 12:08.728
living in devoted service

12:08.762 --> 12:11.498
to a man who won't even return
his phone calls.

12:11.731 --> 12:13.266
Okay. Just--you're just drunk.

12:13.300 --> 12:14.968
<i>It's enough. Another drunk.</i>

12:15.001 --> 12:16.002
<i>Martha's on another--</i>

12:16.036 --> 12:17.971
Blow it out your ass, Mitchell!

12:18.004 --> 12:19.005
- Yeah.
- Huh?

12:19.039 --> 12:20.373
Yeah.

12:20.407 --> 12:22.209
I've been watching you for months
just sitting around here,

12:22.242 --> 12:24.344
staring at the phone
like some teenage girl,

12:24.377 --> 12:28.815
waiting for a call from the boy
with the magic fingers.

12:28.849 --> 12:32.252
When are you gonna get it
through your thick fucking skull

12:32.285 --> 12:36.156
that nobody
on the whole fucking planet

12:36.189 --> 12:38.792
gives a goddamn what you think?

12:38.825 --> 12:40.327
Plenty of people care
what I think.

12:40.360 --> 12:44.030
Barbara Walters wants me
on the <i>Today</i> show to tell my story.

12:44.064 --> 12:45.432
Huh? My story!

12:45.465 --> 12:48.468
They're just looking
for a fucking sideshow!

12:48.502 --> 12:51.304
And that's you, lady!

12:51.338 --> 12:53.073
Do you know why Dick
hasn't called you back,

12:53.106 --> 12:55.108
why he hasn't made any effort
at all to contact you?

12:55.142 --> 12:56.877
Oh, fuck off!

12:56.910 --> 12:59.312
Because he doesn't give a shit.

12:59.346 --> 13:02.449
He never gave a shit
about you, ever!

13:04.317 --> 13:06.820
You think you're so much better
than the rest of them, right?

13:06.853 --> 13:07.854
Don't you?

13:07.888 --> 13:10.457
Dean, Magruder, Haldeman.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.359
Oh, they're just in it
for the money or ambition,

13:12.392 --> 13:14.161
but you're the only one

13:14.194 --> 13:17.898
dumb enough to think
you actually matter to Dick,

13:17.931 --> 13:20.834
that he valued your friendship.

13:20.867 --> 13:23.170
Hey, Martha, I am warning you--

13:23.203 --> 13:26.239
You have ruined everything
in your life, in my life!

13:26.273 --> 13:30.477
Your reputation, your marriage,
and for what?

13:30.510 --> 13:31.811
For what?

13:31.845 --> 13:34.080
I can't stand the sound
of your voice!

13:34.114 --> 13:35.415
Well, that makes two of us!

13:35.448 --> 13:38.018
- I can't stand to look at you!
- I can't stand you!

13:38.051 --> 13:41.288
- I can't stand your face!
- Get fucking off of me!

13:41.321 --> 13:43.823
<i>I love you, Martha,</i>

13:43.857 --> 13:47.460
'cause you're America's clown
and you're a pig.

13:47.494 --> 13:50.497
And all your moaning
and bitching

13:50.530 --> 13:52.165
<i>and your morning drinking</i>

13:52.199 --> 13:56.236
<i>and your day drinking
and your night drinking,</i>

13:56.269 --> 13:59.172
and your own daughter
has to fish you out of the tub

13:59.206 --> 14:02.475
'cause you're too stoned
on pills and booze to stand.

14:02.509 --> 14:03.877
Whose idea were the pills?

14:03.910 --> 14:05.078
- To stand!
- Who?

14:05.111 --> 14:06.379
I thought it would help you!

14:06.413 --> 14:09.282
I didn't know you were gonna
eat them like M&M's!

14:09.316 --> 14:11.218
It's the only way I can sleep
in my bed

14:11.251 --> 14:13.220
when it smells
like your whores.

14:13.253 --> 14:15.222
Oh, you fucking bitch.

14:15.255 --> 14:19.025
I should have had them
go harder on you in California.

14:21.428 --> 14:24.164
- What did you just say?
- Yeah, you heard me.

14:24.197 --> 14:27.867
Even you can't be
so fucking dense

14:27.901 --> 14:32.105
as to think that this was just
an overzealous bodyguard.

14:33.173 --> 14:36.076
<i>You're a cheap joke, Martha.</i>

14:36.109 --> 14:38.578
<i>And every fucking word</i>

14:38.612 --> 14:41.348
that comes out of your mouth

14:41.381 --> 14:45.952
humiliates you
and humiliates me.

14:49.256 --> 14:51.224
<i>Is it--</i>

14:51.258 --> 14:52.392
- See, no.
- No.

14:52.425 --> 14:54.594
- <i>No, no.</i>
- No.

14:54.628 --> 14:58.565
I'm leaving you,
and I'm taking Marty with me.

15:00.300 --> 15:03.670
<i>I'm not going to let her
watch you melt the fuck down.</i>

15:05.572 --> 15:07.540
No.

15:07.574 --> 15:09.276
No. No, you will not.

15:09.309 --> 15:11.011
You can't take her.

15:11.044 --> 15:13.079
You can't--wait.

15:13.113 --> 15:15.949
Mitchell,
you will not take my daughter.

15:15.982 --> 15:19.919
You--I know what you've done.
I'll tell everyone.

15:19.953 --> 15:22.055
You and Dick, both of you,

15:22.088 --> 15:23.690
worse than the break-in
at Watergate,

15:23.923 --> 15:25.292
worse than anyone knows.

15:29.162 --> 15:32.299
And who the hell is gonna
believe you, Martha,

15:32.332 --> 15:34.000
after all this?

15:34.034 --> 15:36.970
Who's gonna believe
little Martha?

15:37.003 --> 15:41.975
I'm just realizing this is my
favorite new position with you.

15:42.008 --> 15:43.443
What's that, Martha?

15:43.476 --> 15:45.412
You're gonna have to speak up,

15:45.445 --> 15:48.315
'cause for once,
I can't hear you.

16:01.695 --> 16:03.630
Go back to your room, honey.

16:08.168 --> 16:09.703
Oh, I love this.
This is great.

16:09.736 --> 16:11.171
<i>How groovy.</i>

16:11.204 --> 16:12.272
Yeah, maybe we could do

16:12.305 --> 16:13.973
<i>a little uh, shaken not stirred.</i>

16:14.007 --> 16:15.208
<i>That's great.</i>

16:15.241 --> 16:17.377
Hey, sweetheart,
can you fix his hair?

16:17.410 --> 16:19.079
<i>Right on.</i>

16:19.112 --> 16:20.280
<i>Just one thing more.</i>

16:20.313 --> 16:21.514
I'm the first married woman
in <i>Playboy.</i>

16:23.583 --> 16:26.586
Great. Um, could you put
your arm around her?

16:28.088 --> 16:29.089
<i>Yeah.</i>

16:30.690 --> 16:32.726
Gotta say, Mr. Dean,
for a man who just went through

16:32.759 --> 16:34.260
a nationally televised gauntlet,

16:34.294 --> 16:36.096
you seem to be
in incredible spirits.

16:36.129 --> 16:37.330
